1
00:00:43,041 --> 00:00:44,375
[KOKONE]
Here I, uh,

2
00:00:44,458 --> 00:00:46,166
I w-washed it for you.

3
00:00:46,250 --> 00:00:49,125
So it's... it's
nice and c-clean.

4
00:00:49,208 --> 00:00:50,541
The others, too.

5
00:00:50,625 --> 00:00:54,375
I-I don't wear these that
o-often, so, so, you know.

6
00:00:54,458 --> 00:00:55,958
[MAIA]
That is helpful.

7
00:00:58,750 --> 00:00:59,916
Yes?

8
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,166
Oh, nothing.

9
00:01:01,250 --> 00:01:03,791
I was just k-kind
of wondering...

10
00:01:07,166 --> 00:01:09,291
[KOKONE]
...h-ho-how, uh...

11
00:01:09,375 --> 00:01:11,666
...you felt about Akira.

12
00:01:11,750 --> 00:01:14,291
Not sure I follow.

13
00:01:14,375 --> 00:01:15,708
[MAIA]
No, it's impossible.

14
00:01:15,791 --> 00:01:18,083
Surely this creature isn't
aware I'm monitoring him?

15
00:01:18,166 --> 00:01:19,708
My cover is secure.

16
00:01:19,791 --> 00:01:21,833
[gasps]

17
00:01:21,916 --> 00:01:24,375
[KOKONE] What would
possess me to ask that?

18
00:01:24,458 --> 00:01:26,958
Great. Now she's upset
with me. I knew it!

19
00:01:27,041 --> 00:01:29,958
[SHOKO]
A-ha. There you are.

20
00:01:30,041 --> 00:01:32,333
[KOKONE]
Sh-Shoko. I was just...

21
00:01:32,416 --> 00:01:34,750
Verbalism Club
meeting in 5, hon.

22
00:01:37,958 --> 00:01:40,583
Four words, it's
Tanabata Festival time!

23
00:01:40,666 --> 00:01:42,041
Huh? What do you mean?

24
00:01:42,125 --> 00:01:44,833
It's August. Isn't all
that stuff over with?

25
00:01:44,916 --> 00:01:46,125
It would be, but the Asagaya

26
00:01:46,208 --> 00:01:48,416
Shopping District's still
on the old calendar.

27
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:50,125
Enough people still
appreciate tradition

28
00:01:50,208 --> 00:01:53,250
that the powers that be
hold it in the summer.

29
00:01:53,333 --> 00:01:57,083
And what a glorious
tradition this Festival is!

30
00:01:57,166 --> 00:01:59,416
Thanks to huge support
from local retailers,

31
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:01,958
it's become Asagaya's
largest annual event,

32
00:02:02,041 --> 00:02:04,416
with stalls as far
as the eye can see.

33
00:02:04,500 --> 00:02:05,875
Though, of course, the real draw

34
00:02:05,958 --> 00:02:09,375
is the plethora of marvelous
papier mâché displays!

35
00:02:09,458 --> 00:02:11,166
On the day of, every
store in the district

36
00:02:11,250 --> 00:02:13,291
showcases entries
from local students.

37
00:02:13,375 --> 00:02:14,875
There's an award
for best display,

38
00:02:14,958 --> 00:02:16,750
so competition is fierce.

39
00:02:16,833 --> 00:02:19,416
And naturally, the creativity
involved is breathtaking.

40
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:21,375
[SHOKO] Last year the winner
was a two story tall

41
00:02:21,458 --> 00:02:23,791
papier mâché reproduction
of the Chikuwa Pie Hermit,

42
00:02:23,875 --> 00:02:26,333
from the Lacross Plus anime.

43
00:02:26,416 --> 00:02:29,250
Yes. I recall being
impressed by the quality.

44
00:02:29,333 --> 00:02:31,000
Oh! Wow!

45
00:02:31,083 --> 00:02:32,916
We are proud residents
of the district.

46
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:35,583
As such, we are duty
bound to participate.

47
00:02:35,666 --> 00:02:38,125
One could even go so far
as to call it a mission!

48
00:02:38,208 --> 00:02:40,458
Seems a bit of a stretch.

49
00:02:40,541 --> 00:02:42,958
Listen up! We will represent!

50
00:02:43,041 --> 00:02:44,875
In fact, not only will
the Verbalism Club

51
00:02:44,958 --> 00:02:47,208
make a bold showing in the
papier mâché competition,

52
00:02:47,291 --> 00:02:50,625
we will put on a celebratory
Reading Theatre follies!

53
00:02:50,708 --> 00:02:52,250
R-Reading Theatre?

54
00:02:52,333 --> 00:02:54,625
You mean like, in front
of actual people?

55
00:02:54,708 --> 00:02:56,125
Excuse me, ma'am,
but counting today,

56
00:02:56,208 --> 00:02:57,875
that only gives us a week.

57
00:02:57,958 --> 00:03:01,041
Even if we started right this
instant, we'd never finish!

58
00:03:01,125 --> 00:03:02,625
[SAKURAKO]
So it would seem.

59
00:03:02,708 --> 00:03:06,708
[SAKURAKO giggles] Which is why,
from now until the festival...

60
00:03:06,791 --> 00:03:10,041
...we'll be camping out
right here at Shirobaco!

61
00:03:11,791 --> 00:03:13,041
Camp?

62
00:03:13,125 --> 00:03:16,583
Uh... C-Could be...
It could be fun!

63
00:03:20,458 --> 00:03:23,083
[SOUGON] In times past,
humanity was at one

64
00:03:23,166 --> 00:03:26,041
with the world of truth.
But the written word,

65
00:03:26,125 --> 00:03:30,541
for all we prospered from it,
wrought incalculable suffering.

66
00:05:09,416 --> 00:05:10,875
[BOY 4A yelps]

67
00:05:10,958 --> 00:05:14,375
Kokone Kikogami!
I am madly in love!

68
00:05:14,458 --> 00:05:16,250
[FOOTBALL CLUB MEMBER 4A]
Don't even try it, pencil neck!

69
00:05:16,333 --> 00:05:17,750
I'm crazy about you!

70
00:05:17,833 --> 00:05:19,250
[KENDO CLUB MEMBER 4A]
I beg your pardon!

71
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:23,375
Please, darling, honor me
with a platonic relationship?

72
00:05:23,458 --> 00:05:25,833
[whimpers]

73
00:05:25,916 --> 00:05:27,125
Will you go out with me?

74
00:05:27,208 --> 00:05:29,000
Score a touchdown on my heart!

75
00:05:29,083 --> 00:05:31,166
Choose me! Please.

76
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:33,250
[whimpers]

77
00:05:36,833 --> 00:05:38,125
[BOYS]
I love you!

78
00:05:38,208 --> 00:05:41,750
[gasping] Sorry!

79
00:05:41,833 --> 00:05:43,375
[BOYS]
Kikogami, wait!

80
00:05:44,708 --> 00:05:46,833
[LADY 4A]
Kids these days.

81
00:05:46,916 --> 00:05:49,375
Oh, what I wouldn't
give to be young.

82
00:05:49,458 --> 00:05:51,875
Don'cha think I'm good enough?

83
00:05:51,958 --> 00:05:53,416
[WOMAN 4A]
Maybe.

84
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:55,916
Whaddya say you an' me hit up
the festival together?

85
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,500
Sure, if I can wear my yukata.

86
00:05:59,791 --> 00:06:01,625
[KOKONE]
"I beg you to go," she said.

87
00:06:01,708 --> 00:06:03,708
"To the noble swan, this...

88
00:06:03,791 --> 00:06:05,583
...this lake is a sacred
place of healing and--

89
00:06:05,666 --> 00:06:07,791
"Silence, bird brains,"
replied the pig.

90
00:06:07,875 --> 00:06:09,041
"Do your eyes fail to see

91
00:06:09,125 --> 00:06:12,416
the Royal Seal of
the Three Brothers?"

92
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:14,958
"Indeed, that shining
pig nose can only

93
00:06:15,041 --> 00:06:16,375
be the legendary..."

94
00:06:16,458 --> 00:06:19,916
[sighs] Real talk for a second:
her acting is atrocious.

95
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,541
It's so endearing!

96
00:06:21,625 --> 00:06:23,125
I know, right? It's perfect!

97
00:06:23,208 --> 00:06:26,541
She's so down to earth!
You wanna root for her!

98
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:30,708
[TANAKA] That's exactly
what I was about to say!

99
00:06:30,791 --> 00:06:31,833
[KOKONE grunts]

100
00:06:31,916 --> 00:06:33,083
[door clicks]

101
00:06:33,166 --> 00:06:34,125
[SHOKO] Thank you for
all the hard work today.

102
00:06:34,208 --> 00:06:35,666
[SAKURAKO]
Of course.

103
00:06:35,750 --> 00:06:38,375
Though, to be fair, I'd say
everyone's giving it their all.

104
00:06:38,458 --> 00:06:40,416
It looks so difficult.

105
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:41,916
[SAKURAKO]
Difficult is good.

106
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:44,500
It helps strengthen the
bond between comrades.

107
00:06:44,583 --> 00:06:47,125
Whole point of
this camp, really.

108
00:06:47,208 --> 00:06:49,291
[yawns]

109
00:06:50,458 --> 00:06:51,750
No yawning, please!

110
00:06:51,833 --> 00:06:53,166
[TSUTOMU]
You don't have to hit me

111
00:06:53,250 --> 00:06:55,458
to get the point across, okay?
What the hell happened

112
00:06:55,541 --> 00:06:57,708
to the sweet little
girl we all adored?

113
00:06:57,791 --> 00:07:00,291
Don't tell me. The cutie
thing was a front.

114
00:07:00,375 --> 00:07:02,458
[KARAN]
Less lip, more teamwork!

115
00:07:02,541 --> 00:07:03,708
So, uh,

116
00:07:03,791 --> 00:07:06,041
there's a question I've
been meaning to ask you.

117
00:07:06,125 --> 00:07:07,291
[AKIRA]
Go for it.

118
00:07:07,375 --> 00:07:09,666
[HAYATO] Why don't I see
that in the blueprint?

119
00:07:11,291 --> 00:07:12,833
Uh--

120
00:07:12,916 --> 00:07:14,750
If she's gonna save the world,
she's gonna need a cool weapon.

121
00:07:14,833 --> 00:07:16,583
Stick to what we all agreed on!

122
00:07:16,666 --> 00:07:19,333
[MAIA chuckles]
You're an imbecile.

123
00:07:21,916 --> 00:07:23,083
[KOKONE]
I-I...

124
00:07:23,166 --> 00:07:24,583
I think it's a neat idea.

125
00:07:24,666 --> 00:07:28,458
I m-mean. S-Saving the
world. I like it.

126
00:07:28,541 --> 00:07:31,250
Hey! Don't go easy on the guy,
you'll give him an ego!

127
00:07:31,333 --> 00:07:34,708
--B-Bu-But, I really mean it.
--[KARAN] Un... deux... trois!

128
00:07:34,791 --> 00:07:37,250
[TSUTOMU]
Ow! Why'd you hit me twice?

129
00:07:38,625 --> 00:07:40,791
One of those was for Kokone.

130
00:07:40,875 --> 00:07:43,166
Ugh! C'mon, people!
Get it in gear!

131
00:07:43,250 --> 00:07:45,000
I think you're getting
a little carried away.

132
00:07:45,083 --> 00:07:45,875
Hee, hee.

133
00:07:45,958 --> 00:07:47,875
Sorry, what do you want from me?

134
00:07:47,958 --> 00:07:50,125
My idol work always
took all my time.

135
00:07:50,208 --> 00:07:52,416
This is my first
ever actual sleepover!

136
00:07:52,500 --> 00:07:53,333
[TSUTOMU]
Yeah, big shock.

137
00:07:53,416 --> 00:07:55,583
Your mother's a total stage mom.

138
00:07:55,666 --> 00:07:58,083
[TSUTOMU grunts]
Stop it.

139
00:07:58,166 --> 00:08:00,375
Thing is, and it's
kinda embarrassing,

140
00:08:00,458 --> 00:08:05,041
I've never had friends to
sleepover with... till now!

141
00:08:05,125 --> 00:08:07,958
Right, guys? So, c'mon!
Make this count.

142
00:08:08,041 --> 00:08:11,833
Let's build a model that'll
take home first prize!

143
00:08:11,916 --> 00:08:12,708
All right, then.

144
00:08:12,791 --> 00:08:14,916
--[beeping]
--[door scrapes]

145
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:17,500
[RANKO]
Sorry. Karan, honey, time to go.

146
00:08:17,583 --> 00:08:19,458
Aw, we're in the
middle of somethin'!

147
00:08:19,541 --> 00:08:22,291
Elementary school idols
end their shenanigans at 8.

148
00:08:22,375 --> 00:08:23,833
I don't make the rules.

149
00:08:23,916 --> 00:08:26,708
[whining] No! I don't
wanna go home!

150
00:08:26,791 --> 00:08:29,958
We're having a sleepover!
Please! I wanna...

151
00:08:30,041 --> 00:08:31,125
Well, that's that.

152
00:08:31,208 --> 00:08:32,541
Seems like.

153
00:08:32,625 --> 00:08:36,125
[TSUTOMU slurps]
When you hear 'bout Tanabata,

154
00:08:36,208 --> 00:08:38,583
it's all Ori-he-man
and Hikoboshi, right?

155
00:08:38,666 --> 00:08:40,875
[HAYATO] Orihime. She's
a princess, not a man.

156
00:08:40,958 --> 00:08:42,666
[TSUTOMU] The two of them
have been the archetypal couple

157
00:08:42,750 --> 00:08:44,833
since, like, before time began.

158
00:08:44,916 --> 00:08:46,750
Y'think they'd be
sick of each other.

159
00:08:46,833 --> 00:08:48,875
[HAYATO]
Such a romantic.

160
00:08:48,958 --> 00:08:50,583
It's so s-sad.

161
00:08:50,666 --> 00:08:51,458
[TSUTOMU]
Hm?

162
00:08:51,541 --> 00:08:53,375
[KOKONE]
O-Ori... Orihime...

163
00:08:53,458 --> 00:08:58,750
...a-and Hikob-boshi are
both so b-beautiful.

164
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:04,083
[KOKONE]
Orihime and Hikoboshi are both

165
00:09:04,166 --> 00:09:06,500
very beautiful stars.

166
00:09:06,583 --> 00:09:09,625
I think there must be a lot
of stars around them

167
00:09:09,708 --> 00:09:11,208
that love them.

168
00:09:11,291 --> 00:09:15,583
Despite that, the two of them
only have eyes for each other.

169
00:09:15,666 --> 00:09:18,250
I feel bad for the other stars.

170
00:09:19,333 --> 00:09:20,541
[gasps]

171
00:09:23,791 --> 00:09:25,666
[HAYATO]
I say we call it a night.

172
00:09:25,750 --> 00:09:27,791
The guys will sleep in the café.

173
00:09:27,875 --> 00:09:31,333
[MAIA] Guess we ladies'll
take the Digibaco.

174
00:09:31,416 --> 00:09:32,875
[KOKONE gasps]

175
00:09:32,958 --> 00:09:34,291
Is something the matter?

176
00:09:34,375 --> 00:09:38,916
[KOKONE]
N-No. I left a thing at-at home.

177
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:43,666
I... should... go and
get it. 'Scuse me.

178
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:45,208
[gasps]

179
00:09:45,291 --> 00:09:46,958
No prob. I'll come with you.

180
00:09:47,041 --> 00:09:48,000
[KOKONE]
Huh?

181
00:09:48,083 --> 00:09:49,250
Good call.

182
00:09:49,333 --> 00:09:51,125
Not a gold star idea for
a young gal to be out

183
00:09:51,208 --> 00:09:53,208
by her lonesome
this time o' night.

184
00:09:53,291 --> 00:09:58,083
N-No! It's fine!
It's n-not far. Promise.

185
00:09:58,166 --> 00:10:01,666
Seriously, it's not a
big deal. I can go myself.

186
00:10:01,750 --> 00:10:03,791
I... I appreciate it, but...

187
00:10:03,875 --> 00:10:05,375
[AKIRA]
What did you forget?

188
00:10:05,458 --> 00:10:07,000
[KOKONE whimpers]

189
00:10:09,583 --> 00:10:12,250
[KOKONE]
I forgot my underwear.

190
00:10:12,333 --> 00:10:13,500
Understood.

191
00:10:13,583 --> 00:10:16,000
You're welcome to borrow mine.

192
00:10:16,083 --> 00:10:17,500
Really?

193
00:10:17,583 --> 00:10:18,625
Why not?

194
00:10:18,708 --> 00:10:20,000
[AKIRA]
'Kay. I'm on it.

195
00:10:20,083 --> 00:10:22,750
Huh?! P-Please don't go!

196
00:10:22,833 --> 00:10:25,625
[AKIRA]
I'm The Savior. It's what I do.

197
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:28,833
--[gasps, whimpers]
--[door scrapes]

198
00:10:30,333 --> 00:10:32,833
I can't quite put
my finger on it.

199
00:10:32,916 --> 00:10:35,625
But that man
sincerely bothers me.

200
00:10:45,875 --> 00:10:47,916
Hey, A-Akira, do you...

201
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:51,166
I mean, do you think
I, um, that I...

202
00:10:51,250 --> 00:10:52,791
That you what?

203
00:10:52,875 --> 00:10:57,041
Well, that I, t-- that I,
t-- t-talk funny or...

204
00:10:58,875 --> 00:11:01,166
Wh-When I was little,

205
00:11:01,250 --> 00:11:04,083
I didn't used to
speak like this, but...

206
00:11:04,166 --> 00:11:07,583
But then...
S-Something happened.

207
00:11:07,666 --> 00:11:10,833
I actually d-dream of
being an a-actress one day.

208
00:11:10,916 --> 00:11:14,000
I w-wanna get up in front
of a b-big audience.

209
00:11:14,083 --> 00:11:16,083
'Cept if I t-talk funny...

210
00:11:16,166 --> 00:11:20,416
...th-then... n-no
one will listen.

211
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:24,708
As long as I'm,
you know, l-like this...

212
00:11:24,791 --> 00:11:28,708
My voice won't... My voice
won't reach anybody.

213
00:11:28,791 --> 00:11:29,666
[AKIRA]
That's not true.

214
00:11:29,750 --> 00:11:31,083
[KOKONE gasps]

215
00:11:31,166 --> 00:11:32,583
Just think.

216
00:11:32,666 --> 00:11:35,041
Your voice had no trouble
reaching me when it mattered.

217
00:11:35,125 --> 00:11:35,583
[yelps]

218
00:11:35,666 --> 00:11:37,375
[KOKONE gasps]

219
00:11:37,458 --> 00:11:39,000
Help!

220
00:11:39,083 --> 00:11:42,416
[AKIRA] You called to me.
You led me here.

221
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:45,333
Your voice is why I'm
where I need to be.

222
00:11:45,416 --> 00:11:48,083
A place where I can
save the world.

223
00:11:48,166 --> 00:11:49,833
I'd call that some reach.

224
00:11:49,916 --> 00:11:52,208
Akira... I...

225
00:11:54,958 --> 00:11:57,541
[SOUGON]
Verbalize. Rejoice.

226
00:11:57,625 --> 00:12:00,666
Today, I deign to set you free!

227
00:12:02,541 --> 00:12:04,875
[M.J.B.K. 4A hissing]

228
00:12:04,958 --> 00:12:06,083
[gasps]

229
00:12:10,166 --> 00:12:14,541
[M.J.B.K. 4A]
Koi!

230
00:12:18,166 --> 00:12:20,208
[KOKONE gasps]

231
00:12:20,291 --> 00:12:22,833
Akira. I...

232
00:12:25,958 --> 00:12:27,458
[KOKONE gasps]

233
00:12:28,875 --> 00:12:30,708
[beeping]

234
00:12:30,791 --> 00:12:33,458
[AKIRA, KOKONE gasp]

235
00:12:33,541 --> 00:12:34,958
[AKIRA]
Ah, hell.

